  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>Yes, you have to request a preview size like "480x800" instead of "800x480" in portrait. You will also need to account for rotation, since the preview frame you get is still relative to the camera's orientation and may need to be 'rotated' to be read. And, the camera's orientation is not necessarily the same on all devices. And it's flipped for front cameras!</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
